transcripts.transcript: So we decided we had to put in a new well, and somebody asked me why I didn't get it wit and I didn't know what he was talking about. So they said there's an old fella out here that witches wells and he'll get you water every time. So I said, OK, uh How much does he want? He wants 10 bucks. I said, bring him on. So we brought this fella out and he went through his maneuvers with his peach stick or I don't remember now it was a peach stick or well, you use both though. Yeah, either 11 works as good as the other. And, uh, he, he, uh strikes a point where, uh, where he has, where he hits water. He puts a stone down and he goes down, uh, in that same line and where he hits water, he put another stone down. Then he goes at right angles with this and he gets a stone over here and the stone over here and where these two lines cross, that's the point of the kind of the veins. He said these water veins always run on an angle. Never do north and south or east and west or northwest. Southeast.
